By default all components that are created in app folder in nextjs are react-server componnets. Which means the initial loading speed in faster as they are rendered in server side.

To Turn server componnets into a client side component we need to use "use client" at the lop of our component file.

When ever we need to use hooks or state we should define the componnet as clent component as state management is handled on the client side.

ISR (Incremental static regeneration): export const regenerate=60 
When the data coming from api is changing/updating continuously, we use this statement at request or page.jsx or layout.jsx level. So that our nextjs server will automatically re fetches the data form api.  

